<doc id="1114869" wikidata="Q376133" url="?curid=1114869" title="Loir">
<text>The Loir is a long river in western France. It is a left tributary of the Sarthe. Its source is in the Eure-et-Loir department, north of Illiers-Combray. It joins the river Sarthe in Briollay, north of the city of Angers.

It is indirectly a tributary of the Loire, and runs roughly parallel to it and slightly north of it for much of its length, and so might be regarded as a Yazoo type river.

==Tributaries==

* Ozanne
* Yerre
* Braye
* Aigre
* Conie

