<doc id="1114986" wikidata="Q5988071" url="?curid=1114986" title="Ideas and Action">
<text>Ideas and Action is an anarcho-syndicalist journal that was founded in 1981 as a result of numerous conferences organized by the New York Metropolitan area Libertarian Workers&#x27; Group and the Syndicalist Alliance of Milwaukee. In 1984, the newly formed Workers Solidarity Alliance took over publication of the journal.

Publication of &quot;Ideas and Action&quot; was suspended after issue #17 (1997). In 2010, an online version of the publication was launched and continues to publish new material.

